    "Name": "Raijin",
    "Details": "The Raijin is designed to be highly mobile and capable of engaging an enemy at a variety of ranges. The Raijin is built around a 300 XL Engine that gives it a top speed of 97.2 km/h. For added mobility, the Raijin carries six jump jets, allowing the 'Mech to jump up to one hundred and eighty meters. The Raijin carries seven tons of Ferro-Fibrous armor. The 'Mech's relatively light armor can be a liability if it is engaged in close combat or finds itself in a protracted engagement. To handle the heat from the weapons onboard, the Raijin carries ten double heat sinks. For long-range striking power, the Raijin carries a ER PPC that can be used to engage a target at up to six hundred and ninety meters. For close combat, the Raijin has three Medium Pulse Lasers. Additionally, to seek out any weak points in an enemy's armor, the Raijin has a SRM-6 and an ammunition efficient Streak SRM-2\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Extended Torso Twist</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.04</color></b>\n\n<br><br><color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limits: Left Upper, Right Upper</color>",
